## Objective
Build a test utility crate for running ftui apps in a PTY and validating terminal behavior.

## Why PTY Tests?
- Verify real terminal behavior (not mocked)
- Test cleanup on panic
- Test cursor restoration
- Validate inline mode works correctly
- Catch issues terminal-model cannot

## PTY Test Capabilities

### Spawn App in PTY
```rust
pub fn spawn_app<F>(f: F) -> PtySession
where F: FnOnce(&mut TerminalSession) -> io::Result<()>
```

- Fork process
- Set up PTY pair
- Run closure in child
- Capture output in parent

### Capture Terminal Output
```rust
impl PtySession {
    fn read_output(&mut self) -> Vec<u8>;
    fn read_until(&mut self, pattern: &[u8], timeout: Duration) -> Result<Vec<u8>>;
    fn send_input(&mut self, bytes: &[u8]);
    fn wait(&mut self) -> ExitStatus;
}
```

### Assert Terminal State
After app exits, verify terminal is restored:
```rust
pub fn assert_terminal_restored(output: &[u8]) {
    // Check for:
    // - SGR 0 (reset style)
    // - CSI ? 25 h (show cursor)
    // - CSI ? 1049 l (exit alt screen) if was used
    // - CSI ? 1000 l (disable mouse) if was enabled
    // - CSI ? 2004 l (disable bracketed paste) if was enabled
}
```

### Test Panic Cleanup
```rust
#[test]
fn panic_cleanup() {
    let session = spawn_app(|term| {
        term.enter_raw_mode()?;
        term.enable_mouse()?;
        panic\!("deliberate panic for testing cleanup");
    });

    let output = session.read_output();
    assert_terminal_restored(&output);
}
```

